<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
AUTO PARTS AND EQUIPMENT INCLUDING TIRES (AUP)
</IN>
<LP>
   MILAN -- Gilardini S.p.A., a diversified parts
manufacturer controlled by auto maker Fiat S.p.A., announced
Thursday it has purchased three manufacturers of car exhaust
systems from ITT Industrie Riunite S.p.A.
   The terms of the transaction weren't disclosed.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The three companies -- Descam Nord SRL, IAO Sud SRL and
ITT Industrie Riunite Sud SRL -- are units of ITT Corp. and
have combined annual sales of 70 billion lire ($60 million)
and a products catalog of some 1,400 items in the area of car
exhaust systems.
   The acquisition reinforces Gilardini's leadership position
in Italy in the production of traditional and catalytic
converters.
</TEXT>
